		"description": "<p>At 10th level, eyes emerge in places where they shouldn&rsquo;t be&mdash;on your limbs, your back, perhaps even on parts of your face. You have advantage on Perception checks that rely on sight and creatures cannot benefit from expertise dice granted by flanking against you.</p>\n<p>Additionally, your extra eyes grant you the ability to see that which others cannot. As an action, you may see invisible creatures and objects and see into the Ethereal Plane for the next hour, as in the spell @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-spells.Item.i7sh0e2wqmql4cac]{See Invisibility}. You may use this ability a number of times equal to half of your proficiency bonus (rounded down) per long rest.</p>",
